tar is an archiver with compression options
archiving and compression are two different things!

archive modi
-c	create
-x	extract

compression filter
-j	bzip2
-z	gzip

informative output
-v	verbose

file and/or device selection
-f	file (--file=archive)

	compr>		none	bzip2	gzip
modus:			----	----	----
create		|	cvf		cvjf	cvzf
extract		|	xvf		xvjf	xvzf

tar -[option] file
